        <h2 style="text-align: center">The Arc&#39;s desire is to support the inclusion of 
            people in their community, not BE their community.</h2><br /><br />
 
    
    
        
   
<h3>Relationships 
        lead to a sense of belonging, love, inclusion, continuity, and meaning to life. 
        Most people find that they value their relationships more highly than anything 
        else in their lives.< People with 
        disabilities are often deprived of both the quantity and quality of 
        relationships that non- disabled people experiences.</h3><br />
    <br /><h2 style="text-align: left">The purpose of Arcin’ Round the 
        Community is to:</h2><br />
    <ul>
        <li>
            <h3>
                Celebrate the wonderful creation of each 
        individual and his/her unique giftedness.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Create community where there has often 
        been isolation, loneliness and brokenness.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Establish and 
        support opportunities for people with disabilities and other community citizens 
        to come together and share common experiences.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Initiate opportunities 
        for people with different abilities to be present and actively participate in 
        the community using the same resources and doing the same activities as other 
        citizens.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Find the places where 
        people come together as citizens – providing access to people who are not 
        functioning as paid professionals but as neighbors’ and citizens.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Build a range of 
        relationships with people with and without disabilities including family, 
        friends, peers and other community members.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Locate 
        common everyday activities and memberships.</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Produce 
        opportunities to do new and interesting things</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Provide opportunities to have 
        contact with people in the community including people and organizations with and 
        ethnic traditions in common</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Assist 
        in discovering what people have in common</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Establish opportunities where 
        common interest and routines can be shared between people with disabilities and 
        other community members</h3>
        </li><br />
        <li>
            <h3>
                Encourage natural 
        supports between people with disabilities, co-workers and other community 
        members</h3>
        </li><br />
</div>
